{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"88c189a5-a834-417d-8511-81c0cce61203","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes** (everything moves after `--`):\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter` | `--filter` (same) |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\nAlso set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in your test `.csproj` so `dotnet test` forwards to the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e857fb90-9cf3-43bb-9cc1-e4184e23dcb4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `--filter` → `--filter`(same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, `dotnet test` still works in .NET 8+, but the command-line arguments have changed significantly, and I need to clarify how the argument forwarding works between the CLI and the new testing platform. I'm realizing that with the newer `dotnet test` integration in .NET 9+, the platform can handle these arguments directly without needing the `--` separator, making the syntax cleaner and more intuitive than the workaround approach I was initially describing. I need to clarify how `dotnet test` actually handles Microsoft.Testing.Platform arguments in .NET 8—the filtering works through `dotnet test`, but other platform-specific options like coverage format, crash dumps, and hang dump timeouts need to be passed correctly through the command line.","outputTokens":1382},"id":"f1cb1161-b2a3-4ec5-bd29-49fd178d005a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:22:43.049Z","parentId":"b0d4ea27-b576-4833-82b8-b8675aba8418"}
